  "id": "batavia",
  "title": "Plan of the Castle and City of Batavia, Capital of the Dutch East Indies",
  "survey_basis": "After the VOC city plans (Clemendt de Jonghe c.1650, and the 18th-century 'Plattegrond van Batavia' tradition), anchored to surviving points of old Jakarta: the Stadhuis of 1710 (Fatahillah Square), the Kali Besar, and the Portuguese Buitenkerk (Gereja Sion, 1695). The Kasteel and most walls are gone today; placed from the plans against the modern river line.",
